cs.GT, cs.CE, cs.SY, cs.LG, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.GT (Game Theory): The paper uses a congestion game approach to evaluate the performance of the electrical transportation system with multiple classes of vehicles. 
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper proposes the design of incentive mechanisms to foster customer engagement in the electrical transportation system. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper considers the flexibility of EV charging as a significant actor in "Demand Response" mechanisms for the electrical grid. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses optimal tolls to control the electrical transportation system and minimize an environmental cost. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper considers the impact of EVs on urban networks both when driving and charging.
